From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
Date: Fri, 25 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] x86/bugs: speculation barrier after VMSCAPE static call

cachyos/0014 removes the trailing lfence inside clear_bhb_loop and
pushes the speculation barrier to call sites: the asm wrappers gain
"call clear_bhb_loop; lfence", and entry_64.S adds a comment noting
"callers should use a speculation barrier like LFENCE immediately after
a call to this function".

The C call site introduced by the same patch in
arch_exit_to_user_mode_prepare() does not. When vmscape_apply_mitigation
points the static call at clear_bhb_loop (VMSCAPE_MITIGATION_BHB_LOOP
path), the BHB clear is followed by speculation through the entry path
with no barrier between, defeating the mitigation.

Add barrier_nospec() immediately after the static call to match the
guarantee provided by the asm wrappers.

---
 arch/x86/include/asm/entry-common.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/include/asm/entry-common.h b/arch/x86/include/asm/entry-common.h
--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/entry-common.h
+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/entry-common.h
@@ -2,6 +2,7 @@
 #ifndef _ASM_X86_ENTRY_COMMON_H
 #define _ASM_X86_ENTRY_COMMON_H

+#include <linux/nospec.h>
 #include <linux/randomize_kstack.h>
 #include <linux/user-return-notifier.h>
 #include <linux/static_call_types.h>
@@ -96,6 +97,7 @@ static inline void arch_exit_to_user_mode_prepare(struct pt_regs *regs,

 	if (unlikely(this_cpu_read(x86_predictor_flush_exit_to_user))) {
 		static_call_cond(vmscape_predictor_flush)();
+		barrier_nospec();
 		this_cpu_write(x86_predictor_flush_exit_to_user, false);
 	}
 }
--
2.52.0
